Port 80 is forwarded to port 8080 to run giuliopizzini.com on python simple server without sudo (as per http://serverfault.com/questions/112795/how-can-i-run-a-server-on-linux-on-port-80-as-a-normal-user)

Forwarded done by command:

$ iptables -t nat -A PREROUTING -p tcp --dport 80 -j REDIRECT --to-port 8080

python server runs with:

$ python -m SimpleHTTPServer 8080

To delete forwarding:

$ sudo iptables -t nat --line-numbers -n -L
$ sudo iptables -t nat -D PREROUTING <line number>      (where line number comes from line above)
